ECOMMERCE DEVELOPMENT ROADMAP

PHASE 1: Foundation Layer (Identity + Catalog Core)
Goal: Establish user identity, authentication, and product data structure.
Outcome: A basic but functional storefront where users can log in and view products.

1. User & Authentication Service
Why first: Everything else (wishlist, cart, orders) depends on user identity.
Build:
- Firebase/Auth0 or JWT login
- User table (email, firebase_uid, created_at)
- Profile management (optional: name, avatar)
- @require_auth decorator (token verification)
Dependencies: None
Feeds: Wishlist, Cart, Orders, Reviews, Loyalty, Admin

2. Product Catalog Service
Why second: The storefront must know what to sell.
Build:
- Product table (id, name, description, category_id)
- Product variants table (SKU, price_cents, stock)
- Product images table
- Category/brand models
- /api/products, /api/products/:id, /api/categories
Dependencies: None
Feeds: Wishlist, Cart, Orders, Search, Analytics

3. Database & Media Foundation
Why: Enables data persistence and image hosting.
Build:
- SQLite/PostgreSQL integration
- Image upload logic or link to CDN (S3, Cloudinary)
- Static asset serving (frontend images)

PHASE 2: User Interaction Layer (Cart, Wishlist, Profile)
Goal: Enable customer interactions: save favorites, add to cart, view profile.
Outcome: A storefront that behaves like a functional shopping site.

4. Cart Service
Why: Central to any eCommerce flow; customers expect to add products to cart.
Build:
- Guest vs. Authenticated cart
- Merge logic on login
- /api/cart, /api/cart/merge, /api/cart/count
- Stock validation and pricing recalculation
Dependencies: Auth, Product Catalog

5. Wishlist Service
Why: Improves retention and engagement.
Build:
- /api/wishlist, /api/wishlist/merge, /api/wishlist/count
- Guest localStorage sync logic
- Server-side persistence per user
Dependencies: Auth, Product Catalog

6. User Profile & Address Service
Why: Needed before checkout and personalization.
Build:
- /api/users/me, /api/users/me/profile
- /api/address CRUD routes
- Address validation, default flags
Dependencies: Auth

PHASE 3: Transaction Layer (Orders + Payments + Checkout)
Goal: Allow full purchase flow and order lifecycle management.
Outcome: Shoppable platform with order history, confirmations, and payments.

7. Checkout Service
Why: Connects cart → payment → order creation.
Build:
- Checkout session API (/api/checkout/start)
- Validate stock & pricing
- Calculate tax/shipping/discounts
- Create provisional order record
Dependencies: Cart, User Address, Product Catalog

8. Payment Gateway Integration
Why: Enables order confirmation and transaction tracking.
Build:
- Integration with Razorpay, Stripe, PayPal
- /api/payments/intent, /api/payments/callback
- Payment status verification
- Refund initiation endpoint
Dependencies: Checkout, Orders

9. Order Management Service
Why: Core for tracking, support, and admin operations.
Build:
- /api/orders, /api/orders/:id
- Order lines table (product_id, price, qty)
- Order status updates (placed, shipped, delivered)
- Cancellation and returns
Dependencies: Payment, Auth, Product Catalog

PHASE 4: Fulfillment & Logistics
Goal: Enable shipping, delivery, returns, and real-world product movement.

10. Shipping & Fulfillment Service
Build:
- Shipping methods (standard, express)
- Address mapping → shipping zone
- Integration with carrier APIs
- Generate tracking IDs
- Update order statuses automatically
Dependencies: Orders, Address

11. Returns (RMA) Service
Build:
- /api/returns
- Product condition checks
- Refund or replacement workflows
Dependencies: Orders, Payment

PHASE 5: Customer Engagement Layer
Goal: Retain customers through interaction, feedback, and communication.

12. Reviews & Ratings Service
Build:
- /api/reviews CRUD
- Verified purchase flag
- Spam detection and moderation
Dependencies: Auth, Product Catalog, Orders

13. Notifications Service
Build:
- Email, SMS, and push notifications
- Triggers for order status, payment success, etc.
- Preference center (opt-in/out)
Dependencies: Orders, Payment

14. Loyalty & Referral Service
Build:
- Reward points table
- /api/loyalty to fetch and redeem points
- Referral codes and tracking
Dependencies: Auth, Orders

PHASE 6: Marketing, Analytics, and Discovery
Goal: Increase reach, optimize conversions, and improve customer insights.

15. Search & Recommendation Service
Build:
- Full-text search
- Product suggestions (“people also bought…”)
- Recently viewed, trending
Dependencies: Product Catalog, Analytics

16. Promotions & Discounts Service
Build:
- Coupon codes
- Category/brand-level discounts
- Cart-level price rules
Dependencies: Cart, Checkout, Orders

17. Analytics & Reporting Service
Build:
- Track user sessions, purchases, product views
- Funnel analytics (view → cart → purchase)
- Sales, retention, stock insights
- Admin dashboard metrics
Dependencies: All user & order data

PHASE 7: Operations & Administration
Goal: Provide control to manage catalog, users, and operational efficiency.

18. Admin Dashboard Service
Build:
- Role-based access (admin, staff)
- Manage products, orders, users
- Sales and refund reports
- Promotion management
Dependencies: All core services

19. Customer Support Service
Build:
- Ticket management
- Order issue resolution (refunds, missing items)
- Chat integration
- Auto-replies and SLA tracking
Dependencies: Orders, Users

PHASE 8: Infrastructure & Scalability Layer
Goal: Prepare for production-grade load and maintainability.

20. Caching & Performance
Build:
- Redis for cart, product, and wishlist caching
- CDN (Cloudflare, AWS CloudFront) for assets
- Lazy loading for product images

21. Logging & Monitoring
Build:
- Structured logs for every domain
- Alerting (Datadog, Grafana)
- Audit trail for admin actions

22. Security Hardening
Build:
- HTTPS, CORS enforcement
- Rate limiting, CSRF protection
- Token rotation and revocation

Execution Sequence Overview
Phase      Layer            Focus                        Dependencies
1          Foundation       Auth + Catalog                None
2          Interaction      Cart, Wishlist, Profile       Auth, Catalog
3          Transaction      Checkout, Orders, Payment     Cart, Address
4          Fulfillment      Shipping, Returns             Orders
5          Engagement       Reviews, Loyalty, Notifications Orders, Auth
6          Marketing        Search, Promotions, Analytics Catalog, Orders
7          Admin            Dashboard, Support            All prior
8          Infrastructure   Caching, Logging, Security    All prior

Recommended Build Order Summary
Auth + Users
Catalog + Products
Cart + Wishlist
Checkout + Payment + Orders
Addresses + Shipping
Notifications + Reviews + Loyalty
Search + Analytics + Promotions
Admin Dashboard + Customer Support
